snippet.textDisplay: Don't agree with Kyrie, but...the competition from this year to last year can be different. Just because they made the playoffs doesn't mean much unless they had been doing it for years like the spurs or something.  Now these teams have more tape and analysis on how to defend these young players. A case can be made that it's more the coaches fault. They added 3 starters to their lineup who haven't had a chance to play together yet. So they may need more pieces now if they are looking to make a push to the playoffs and past the first round. He was definitely out of line to say this to the media because it's in bad taste. You barely played and judging performance with an incomplete roster. Makes no sense. I was not a big fan of DLO, but honestly I'd rather have him back. I felt he had great momentum coming into this year to be even more of a breakout star, but the organization destroyed that. I am a fan of Kyrie on the court, but just wish he was a bit more humble as he is a new face on the team.
